description: Creates a label for an event.

parameters.name: LabelGroupName
parameters.description: The name of a group of labels. Data in this field will be retained for service usage. Follow best practices for the security of your data.

parameters.name: StartTime
parameters.description: The start time of the labeled event.

parameters.name: EndTime
parameters.description: The end time of the labeled event.

parameters.name: Rating
parameters.description: Indicates whether a labeled event represents an anomaly.

parameters.name: FaultCode
parameters.description: Provides additional information about the label. The fault code must be defined in the FaultCodes attribute of the label group. Data in this field will be retained for service usage. Follow best practices for the security of your data.

parameters.name: Notes
parameters.description: Metadata providing additional information about the label. Data in this field will be retained for service usage. Follow best practices for the security of your data.

parameters.name: Equipment
parameters.description: Indicates that a label pertains to a particular piece of equipment. Data in this field will be retained for service usage. Follow best practices for the security of your data.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: A unique identifier for the request to create a label. If you do not set the client request token, Lookout for Equipment generates one. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

nested_items.name: LabelId
nested_items.description: The ID of the label that you have created.
